The conventional method to evaluate the resolution of an [[tomography]] reconstruction is determined by the '''Crowther criterion'''.<ref name=Crowther>{{cite journal|title=The Reconstruction of a Three-Dimensional Structure from Projections and its Application to Electron Microscopy|year=1970|author1=R. A. Crowther |author2=D. J. DeRosier |author3=A. Klug |journal=Proc. Roy. Soc. Lond. A|volume=317}}</ref> The minimum number of views, ''m'', to reconstruct a particle of diameter ''D'' to a resolution of ''d'' (=1/''R'') is given by
:<math>m = \pi \frac{D}{d}.</math>

