The '''Dutch Hill/Cohocton Wind Farm''' is a 125 [[Megawatt]] [[wind farm]] in [[Cohocton, New York]]. It uses 50 turbines of the [[Liberty Wind Turbine|Clipper "Liberty" type]],<ref>[http://www.cohoctonwind.com/cohocton/about.cfm] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090924114430/http://www.cohoctonwind.com/cohocton/about.cfm |date=September 24, 2009 }}</ref> which were the largest found in the United States when they were put up for sale. The wind farm provides [[electric|power]] for about 50,000 Northeastern homes. The wind farm is located in [[Steuben County, New York|Steuben County]]. It was installed in 2008 and was developed and operated by [[First Wind]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thewindpower.net/wind-farm-4397-dutch-hill-cohocton-wind-farm-clipper-nd.php|title=Cohocton Wind Farm wind farm|work=thewindpower.net}}</ref>

