The ''' Nkenda–Fort Portal–Hoima High Voltage Power Line''' is a high voltage electricity power line, in operation, connecting the high voltage substation at Nkenda, [[Kasese District]], to another high voltage substation at Kabaale, Buseruka sub-county, [[Hoima District]], all in the [[Western Region, Uganda|Western Region]] of [[Uganda]].<ref name="1R">{{cite web| url=https://archives.visiongroup.co.ug/collections/101-oil-minerals-energy/30156-building-of-hoima-power-line-starts | format=Archived from the Original |title=Building of Hoima power line starts |date=20 October 2016 |access-date=24 May 2018 | newspaper=[[New Vision]] |first=Pascal |last=Kwesiga | location=Kampala}}</ref><ref name="3R">{{cite web|author=UETCL | url=http://www.uetcl.com/index.php/site-administrator/2014-01-29-09-43-25 |title=Uganda Electricity Transmission Company Limited: Projects Under Implementation |accessdate=23 December 2017 | date= 29 January 2014 | publisher=[[Uganda Electricity Transmission Company Limited]] (UETCL) |location=Kampala}}</ref>
==Location== The 220 kilo Volt power line starts at the 220kV substation a Nkenda, in [[Kasese District]], approximately {{convert|10|km|0}}, by road, north of [[Kasese]], the district headquarters, and nearest large town.<ref name="4R">{{cite web | author=Distancesfrom.com |publisher=Distancesfrom.com | url=https://www.distancesfrom.com/ug/distance-from-Nkenda-to-Kasese/DistanceHistory/5842929.aspx|title=10 Km - Distance from Nkenda to Kasese |access-date=23 December 2017 |date=23 December 2017}}</ref> The line travels in a north-easterly direction, through [[Fort Portal]], in [[Kabarole District]], to end at Kabaale, in Buseruka sub-county, in [[Hoima District]], a total distance of approximately {{convert|226|km|0}}.<ref name="3R"/>
==Overview== This power line is planned to evacuate the power from a number of mini-hydro power projects in the Western Region districts of [[Bundibugyo District|Bundibugyo]], [[Bunyangabu District|Bunyangabu]], [[Kasese District|Kasese]], [[Hoima District|Hoima]] and [[Masindi District|Masindi]].<ref name="3R"/><ref name="5R">{{cite web|title=France gives $23 million for Fort Portal, Hoima power line |newspaper=[[New Vision]] |access-date=23 December 2017 |date=31 October 2013 | url=https://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1334127/france-usd23m-fort-portal-hoima-power |last=Kasita |first=Ibrahim | location=Kampala}}</ref> It is also planned to evacuate power from the proposed [[Nzizi Thermal Power Station]]. The power that this power line evacuates is sold to the [[Uganda Electricity Transmission Company Limited]] and integrated into the national electric grid.<ref name="6R">{{cite web | url=http://www.monitor.co.ug/Business/France-offers-government-Shs58b-loan/688322-2055914-pni8v1z/index.html| title=France offers government Shs58 billion loan |accessdate=23 December 2017 |date=1 November 2013 |newspaper=[[Daily Monitor]] |first=Paul | last=Tajuba |location=Kampala}}</ref>
==Construction== KEC International is the main contractor for this project. The supervising engineering company is "Ficthner Gmbh". The contract for construction of the associated substations was awarded to "Shan-dong Taikai Power Engineering Company Limited.<ref name="3R"/> The [[government of Norway]] donated US$54 million towards the completion of this project.<ref name="5R"/> In 2013, the Ugandan government borrowed US$23 million from the [[French Development Agency]] to finance this power line.<ref name="5R"/><ref name="6R"/> Construction began in 2016, with completion in July 2018 and public commissioning on 14 August 2018.<ref name="2R"/>
