The '''Vestas V90-2MW''' is a three bladed upwind horizontal axis wind turbine designed and manufactured by [[Vestas]]{{citation needed|date=June 2014}} with versions for [[IEC 61400#Wind Turbine Generator (WTG) Classes ( IEC 61400-1 ed.2)|wind classes]] IIA and IIIA.<ref name=vestas>Product page at vestas.com: {{cite web|url=http://www.vestas.com/en/products_and_services/turbines/v90-2_0_mw|title=V90-2.0 MW|accessdate=11 June 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140625101028/http://vestas.com/en/products_and_services/turbines/v90-2_0_mw|archive-date=2014-06-25|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>

The V90-2MW has a tubular steel tower between {{convert|80|m|ft}} and {{convert|125|m|ft}} height. The [[Nacelle (wind turbine)|nacelle]] is {{convert|10.4|m|ft}} long, {{convert|3.5|m|ft}} wide, and {{convert|5.4|m|ft}} high once installed. The rotor has a diameter of {{convert|90|m|ft}}, with blades {{convert|44|m|ft}} long.<ref name=vestas />

